modules.description: Provides functions to create, manipulate, and access elements of multidimensional arrays, with support for various data types including integers, floats, and strings. Works with Bigarray's array types, offering a unified interface across OCaml versions. Enables efficient numerical computations and data processing in environments where Bigarray is available.

Provides low-level support for working with bigarrays, including element types and layout representations. Defines element kinds via type-level constructors and layout options (C-style or Fortran-style) using a GADT. Allows operations like slicing, blitting, and filling, but requires manual synchronization for concurrent access to avoid data races and inconsistent results. Examples include managing multidimensional data layouts and performing bulk memory operations with awareness of concurrency constraints.
